  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Topological Sort Interactive Demo</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    font-size: 14px;\n    margin: 10px;\n    background: #fff;\n    color: #000;\n  }\n  textarea, input[type=number], input[type=text] {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    font-size: 13px;\n  }\n  button {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    font-size: 13px;\n  }\n  #graphDisplay, #logArea {\n    white-space: pre;\n    border: 1px solid;\n    padding: 5px;\n    height: 150px;\n    overflow: auto;\n    background: #fff;\n  }\n  #stepControls > * {\n    margin-top: 4px;\n    margin-right: 6px;\n  }\n  table {\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n  }\n  td, th {\n    border: 1px solid #000;\n    padding: 2px 6px;\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h2>Topological Sort Interactive Demo</h2>\n\n<p>\nThis demo lets you define a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) in multiple ways, and explore\ntopological sorting with maximum user control and exploration.\n</p>\n\n<section>\n  <h3>1. Graph Input / Construction</h3>\n  <p><b>Methods to build or edit the graph:</b></p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Manually add/remove edges</li>\n    <li>Load sample graphs</li>\n    <li>Paste adjacency list</li>\n  </ul>\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"vertexNameInp\">New Vertex Name:</label>\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"vertexNameInp\" size=\"4\" maxlength=\"10\" />\n    <button id=\"addVertexBtn\">Add Vertex</button>\n    <button id=\"clearGraphBtn\">Clear Graph</button>\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:7px;\">\n    <label for=\"fromVertexInp\">From:</label>\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"fromVertexInp\" size=\"4\" maxlength=\"10\" />\n    <label for=\"toVertexInp\">To:</label>\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"toVertexInp\" size=\"4\" maxlength=\"10\" />\n    <button id=\"addEdgeBtn\">Add Edge</button>\n    <button id=\"removeEdgeBtn\">Remove Edge</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"loadSampleSelect\">Load Sample Graph:</label>\n    <select id=\"loadSampleSelect\">\n      <option value=\"\">-- Select Sample --</option>\n      <option value=\"basicDAG\">Basic DAG (ABCDE)</option>\n      <option value=\"diamond\">Diamond Shape</option>\n      <option value=\"complex\">Complex DAG (10 nodes)</option>\n      <option value=\"cycle\">Graph with a Cycle (Bad Input)</option>\n    </select>\n    <button id=\"loadSampleBtn\">Load Sample</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"pasteAdjacencyArea\">Paste adjacency list (one vertex and edges per line):</label><br />\n    <textarea id=\"pasteAdjacencyArea\" cols=\"50\" rows=\"6\" placeholder=\"A: B C&#10;B: C&#10;C:\"></textarea><br />\n    <button id=\"loadAdjacencyBtn\">Load Graph From Adjacency</button>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n  <h3>2. Graph Display</h3>\n  <div id=\"graphDisplay\" aria-label=\"Graph adjacency display\"></div>\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n  <h3>3. Topological Sort Exploration Controls</h3>\n  <p>\n    <b>Instructions:</b><br />\n    - Use the buttons below to run or step through a topological sort.<br />\n    - You can choose the algorithm (Kahn or DFS).<br />\n    - You may manually pick which node to remove next if multiple choices exist.<br />\n    - Detect and explore cycles interactively.<br />\n    - Reset and re-run as you like.\n  </p>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"algoSelect\">Algorithm:</label>\n    <select id=\"algoSelect\" aria-label=\"Select topological sort algorithm\">\n      <option value=\"kahn\">Kahn's Algorithm (BFS)</option>\n      <option value=\"dfs\">DFS Based Algorithm</option>\n    </select>\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"stepControls\" style=\"margin-top:6px;\">\n    <button id=\"initRunBtn\">Initialize Sort</button>\n    <button id=\"stepBtn\" disabled>Next Step</button>\n    <button id=\"autoRunBtn\" disabled>Auto Run</button>\n    <button id=\"pauseAutoBtn\" disabled>Pause Auto Run</button>\n    <button id=\"resetSortBtn\" disabled>Reset Sort</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"autoRunSpeed\">Auto run speed (ms per step):</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"autoRunSpeed\" value=\"1000\" min=\"50\" max=\"5000\" step=\"50\" />\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"manualPickSelect\">Manual Pick Among Available Nodes:</label>\n    <select id=\"manualPickSelect\" size=\"5\" style=\"width:150px\" aria-label=\"Manual pick node from available set\" disabled></select>\n    <button id=\"pickNodeBtn\" disabled>Pick Selected Node</button>\n  </div>\n\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n  <h3>4. Sort State & Logs</h3>\n  <div>\n    <b>Current Sort Order:</b>\n    <div id=\"currentOrderDisplay\" style=\"min-height:20px; margin:3px 0; white-space:pre-wrap;\"></div>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <b>Available Nodes for Next Step:</b>\n    <div id=\"availableNodesDisplay\" style=\"min-height:20px; margin:3px 0;\"></div>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <b>Internal State (Debug Info):</b>\n    <div id=\"stateDisplay\" style=\"min-height:60px; overflow:auto; white-space:pre-wrap; border:1px solid;\"></div>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <b>Log / Messages:</b>\n    <div id=\"logArea\" aria-live=\"polite\"></div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<section>\n  <h3>5. Extras</h3>\n  <div>\n    <button id=\"exportGraphBtn\">Export Graph as JSON</button>\n    <button id=\"importGraphBtn\">Import Graph JSON (Paste JSON below and press Import)</button>\n  </div>\n  <textarea id=\"importExportArea\" cols=\"50\" rows=\"6\" placeholder='{\"vertices\":[\"A\",\"B\"],\"edges\":{\"A\":[\"B\"],\"B\":[]}}'></textarea>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  \"use strict\";\n\n  // Graph data structure: \n  // vertices: array of strings (vertex ids)\n  // edges: object mapping vertex id -> array of vertex ids for edges from vertex\n  // Graph must not have duplicate vertices.\n  // This is a DAG, but user may input invalid graphs.\n\n  class Graph {\n    constructor() {\n      this.vertices = [];\n      this.edges = {};\n    }\n\n    clear() {\n      this.vertices = [];\n      this.edges = {};\n    }\n\n    hasVertex(v) {\n      return this.vertices.includes(v);\n    }\n\n    addVertex(v) {\n      if (!this.hasVertex(v)) {\n        this.vertices.push(v);\n        this.edges[v] = [];\n        return true;\n      }\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    removeVertex(v) {\n      const idx = this.vertices.indexOf(v);\n      if(idx < 0) return false;\n      this.vertices.splice(idx,1);\n      delete this.edges[v];\n      for(let from of this.vertices) {\n        const arr = this.edges[from];\n        const i = arr.indexOf(v);\n        if(i >= 0) {\n          arr.splice(i,1);\n        }\n      }\n      return true;\n    }\n\n    addEdge(from, to) {\n      if (!this.hasVertex(from) || !this.hasVertex(to)) return false;\n      if (!this.edges[from].includes(to)) {\n        this.edges[from].push(to);\n        return true;\n      }\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    removeEdge(from, to) {\n      if (!this.hasVertex(from) || !this.hasVertex(to)) return false;\n      const idx = this.edges[from].indexOf(to);\n      if (idx >= 0) {\n        this.edges[from].splice(idx,1);\n        return true;\n      }\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    getEdgesFrom(v) {\n      return this.edges[v] || [];\n    }\n\n    clone() {\n      const g = new Graph();\n      for(let v of this.vertices) g.addVertex(v);\n      for(let v of this.vertices) {\n        for(let w of this.edges[v]) {\n          g.addEdge(v,w);\n        }\n      }\n      return g;\n    }\n\n    // Returns boolean - true if cycle detected\n    // Optional: return the actual cycle path.\n    detectCycle() {\n      const visited = new Set();\n      const stack = new Set();\n\n      const vertices = this.vertices;\n\n      const edges = this.edges;\n\n      let cycleFound = false;\n\n      let cyclePath = [];\n\n      // DFS to detect cycle\n      function dfs(u, path) {\n        if(cycleFound) return;\n        visited.add(u);\n        stack.add(u);\n        path.push(u);\n        for(let w of edges[u]) {\n          if(!visited.has(w)) {\n            dfs(w, path);\n          }\n          else if(stack.has(w)) {\n            // cycle found from w to current u\n            cycleFound = true;\n            // Find the cycle path from w onwards in path\n            const cycleStartIndex = path.indexOf(w);\n            cyclePath = path.slice(cycleStartIndex);\n            cyclePath.push(w); // complete cycle\n            return;\n          }\n          if(cycleFound) return;\n        }\n        stack.delete(u);\n        path.pop();\n      }\n\n      for(let v of vertices) {\n        if(!visited.has(v)) {\n          dfs(v, []);\n          if(cycleFound) break;\n        }\n      }\n\n      return cycleFound ? cyclePath : null;\n    }\n\n    // Build and return adjacency representation string (sorted vertices and edges)\n    toAdjacencyString() {\n      const verts = [...this.vertices].sort();\n      let out = '';\n      for(let v of verts) {\n        let edgesSorted = [...this.edges[v]].sort();\n        out += v + ': ' + (edgesSorted.length ? edgesSorted.join(' ') : '') + '\\n';\n      }\n      return out;\n    }\n\n    // Return indegree map {vertex: integer}\n    indegreeMap() {\n      const indeg = {};\n      for(let v of this.vertices) indeg[v] = 0;\n      for(let v of this.vertices) {\n        for(let w of this.edges[v]) indeg[w]++;\n      }\n      return indeg;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // GLOBAL State and UI Elements\n  const graph = new Graph();\n\n  // UI Elements\n  const vertexNameInp = document.getElementById('vertexNameInp');\n  const addVertexBtn = document.getElementById('addVertexBtn');\n  const clearGraphBtn = document.getElementById('clearGraphBtn');\n\n  const fromVertexInp = document.getElementById('fromVertexInp');\n  const toVertexInp = document.getElementById('toVertexInp');\n  const addEdgeBtn = document.getElementById('addEdgeBtn');\n  const removeEdgeBtn = document.getElementById('removeEdgeBtn');\n\n  const loadSampleSelect = document.getElementById('loadSampleSelect');\n  const loadSampleBtn = document.getElementById('loadSampleBtn');\n\n  const pasteAdjacencyArea = document.getElementById('pasteAdjacencyArea');\n  const loadAdjacencyBtn = document.getElementById('loadAdjacencyBtn');\n\n  const graphDisplay = document.getElementById('graphDisplay');\n\n  const algoSelect = document.getElementById('algoSelect');\n\n  const initRunBtn = document.getElementById('initRunBtn');\n  const stepBtn = document.getElementById('stepBtn');\n  const autoRunBtn = document.getElementById('autoRunBtn');\n  const pauseAutoBtn = document.getElementById('pauseAutoBtn');\n  const resetSortBtn = document.getElementById('resetSortBtn');\n\n  const autoRunSpeedInp = document.getElementById('autoRunSpeed');\n\n  const manualPickSelect = document.getElementById('manualPickSelect');\n  const pickNodeBtn = document.getElementById('pickNodeBtn');\n\n  const currentOrderDisplay = document.getElementById('currentOrderDisplay');\n  const availableNodesDisplay = document.getElementById('availableNodesDisplay');\n  const logArea = document.getElementById('logArea');\n  const stateDisplay = document.getElementById('stateDisplay');\n\n  const exportGraphBtn = document.getElementById('exportGraphBtn');\n  const importGraphBtn = document.getElementById('importGraphBtn');\n  const importExportArea = document.getElementById('importExportArea');\n\n  // Topological Sort controller state & behavior\n\n  // Supported algorithms:\n  // \"kahn\" - Kahn's algorithm (queue of zero indegree nodes)\n  // \"dfs\" - DFS based (ordering by finishing times, detect cycle if visiting vertex again)\n\n  class SortController {\n    constructor(graph) {\n      this.graph = graph.clone();\n\n      this.algo = 'kahn';\n\n      // common state to track sort progress\n      this.finished = false;\n      this.hasCycle = false;\n      this.cycleInfo = null;\n\n      // For Kahn's algorithm\n      this.indeg = {};\n      this.available = []; // nodes with indegree zero\n      this.order = [];\n\n      // For DFS algorithm\n      this.visited = new Set();\n      this.recStack = new Set();\n      this.dfsOrder = [];\n      this.dfsStack = [];\n      this.dfsIterator = null;\n      this.dfsCurrent = null;\n\n      // Manual pick mode (when multiple possible nodes)\n      this.manualPickMode = false;\n\n      // For controlling auto run\n      this.autorun = false;\n    }\n\n    setAlgorithm(algo) {\n      this.algo = algo;\n    }\n\n    // Initialize or reset internal structures for running the sort\n    init() {\n      this.finished = false;\n      this.hasCycle = false;\n      this.cycleInfo = null;\n\n      this.order = [];\n\n      this.manualPickMode = false;\n\n      this.autorun = false;\n\n      if(this.algo === 'kahn') {\n        // Compute indegree map\n        this.indeg = this.graph.indegreeMap();\n        // Initialize available array with all vertices zero indegree\n        this.available = [];\n        for(let v of this.graph.vertices) {\n          if(this.indeg[v] === 0) this.available.push(v);\n        }\n        // Sort available alphabetically for consistent order\n        this.available.sort();\n      }\n      else if(this.algo === 'dfs') {\n        this.visited = new Set();\n        this.recStack = new Set();\n        this.dfsOrder = [];\n        this.dfsStack = [];\n        this.dfsIterator = null;\n        this.dfsCurrent = null;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Return a snapshot info object with current detailed state for display\n    getStateSnapshot() {\n      if(this.algo === 'kahn') {\n        return {\n          order: [...this.order],\n          available: [...this.available],\n          indeg: {...this.indeg},\n          finished: this.finished,\n          hasCycle: this.hasCycle,\n          cycleInfo: this.cycleInfo,\n          manualPickMode: this.manualPickMode\n        };\n      }\n      else if(this.algo === 'dfs') {\n        return {\n          order: [...this.dfsOrder],\n          visited: Array.from(this.visited).sort(),\n          recStack: Array.from(this.recStack).sort(),\n          dfsStack: [...this.dfsStack],\n          dfsCurrent: this.dfsCurrent,\n          finished: this.finished,\n          hasCycle: this.hasCycle,\n          cycleInfo: this.cycleInfo,\n          manualPickMode: false\n        };\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Kahn's algorithm step: remove one node from available and update indegree, add new nodes to available.\n    // Returns a message string describing step or null if done.\n    stepKahn(optionalSelectNode=null) {\n      if(this.finished) {\n        return \"Sort is already finished.\";\n      }\n      if(this.available.length === 0) {\n        // No available nodes -> if order.length < total vertices means cycle\n        if(this.order.length < this.graph.vertices.length) {\n          this.hasCycle = true;\n          this.cycleInfo = this.graph.detectCycle(); // get cycle path\n          this.finished = true;\n          return \"Cycle detected, topological sort not possible.\";\n        }\n        else {\n          this.finished = true;\n          return \"Topological sort finished successfully.\";\n        }\n      }\n      // Check manual pick mode\n      if(this.available.length > 1) {\n        if(optionalSelectNode === null) {\n          this.manualPickMode = true;\n          return \"Multiple nodes available, waiting for manual pick.\";\n        }\n        else {\n          if(!this.available.includes(optionalSelectNode)) {\n            return \"Selected node is not available.\";\n          }\n          else {\n            // manual choice selected\n            this.manualPickMode = false;\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      else {\n        // Only one option, must use automatically\n        optionalSelectNode = this.available[0];\n      }\n      // Process the chosen node\n      const u = optionalSelectNode;\n      // Remove u from available\n      const idx = this.available.indexOf(u);\n      this.available.splice(idx,1);\n      this.order.push(u);\n\n      // Decrement indegree of neighbors\n      for(let w of this.graph.edges[u]) {\n        this.indeg[w]--;\n        if(this.indeg[w] === 0) {\n          this.available.push(w);\n        }\n      }\n      // Sort available for consistency\n      this.available.sort();\n\n      // Check termination\n      if(this.available.length === 0 && this.order.length < this.graph.vertices.length) {\n        this.hasCycle = true;\n        this.cycleInfo = this.graph.detectCycle(); // try to detect cycle\n        this.finished = true;\n        return \"Cycle detected, topological sort not possible.\";\n      }\n      if(this.order.length === this.graph.vertices.length){\n        this.finished = true;\n        return \"Topological sort finished successfully.\";\n      }\n\n      return \"Removed node \"+u+\" from queue.\";\n    }\n\n    // DFS algorithm initialization, uses iterative approach here for deep exploration\n    initDFS() {\n      this.visited = new Set();\n      this.recStack = new Set();\n      this.dfsOrder = [];\n      this.dfsStack = [];\n      this.dfsIterator = null;\n      this.dfsCurrent = null;\n      this.finished = false;\n      this.hasCycle = false;\n      this.cycleInfo = null;\n\n      // We start with the lex smallest vertex not visited\n      this.dfsStack = [];\n\n      // Start DFS on smallest vertex\n      // We track manually which vertices were started to DFS\n      this.unvisitedStack = [...this.graph.vertices].sort();\n      this.dfsCurrent = null;\n    }\n\n    // DFS iterative step; returns message\n    stepDFS() {\n      if(this.finished) {\n        return \"Sort already finished.\";\n      }\n      // If no current DFS path and there are unvisited vertices, start new DFS from lex smallest unvisited\n      if(this.dfsStack.length === 0 && this.unvisitedStack.length === 0) {\n        // All done\n        this.orderFromDFS();\n        this.finished = true;\n        return \"Topological sort finished successfully.\";\n      }\n      if(this.dfsStack.length === 0) {\n        // Start DFS from vertex in unvisited stack\n        while(this.unvisitedStack.length > 0) {\n          const u = this.unvisitedStack.shift();\n          if(!this.visited.has(u)) {\n            this.dfsStack.push({\n              vertex: u,\n              neighbors: [...this.graph.edges[u]].sort(),\n              childIndex: 0,\n            });\n            this.recStack.add(u);\n            this.dfsCurrent = u;\n            return \"Started DFS from vertex \"+u+\".\";\n          }\n        }\n        // No unvisited left -> done\n        this.orderFromDFS();\n        this.finished = true;\n        return \"Topological sort finished successfully.\";\n      }\n      // Continue DFS with top of dfsStack\n      let frame = this.dfsStack[this.dfsStack.length-1];\n      const u = frame.vertex;\n      const neighbors = frame.neighbors;\n      const idx = frame.childIndex;\n\n      if(idx >= neighbors.length) {\n        // Finished exploring all neighbors -> pop stack\n        // Mark u as fully explored\n        this.dfsStack.pop();\n        this.recStack.delete(u);\n        this.visited.add(u);\n        this.dfsOrder.unshift(u); // prepend to order - finishing time order\n\n        // Update dfsStack and current dfsCurrent\n        this.dfsCurrent = this.dfsStack.length > 0 ? this.dfsStack[this.dfsStack.length-1].vertex : null;\n\n        if(this.dfsStack.length === 0 && this.unvisitedStack.length === 0) {\n          this.orderFromDFS();\n          this.finished = true;\n          return \"Topological sort finished successfully.\";\n        }\n        return \"Completed DFS for vertex \"+u+\".\";\n      }\n      else {\n        // Explore next neighbor\n        const w = neighbors[idx];\n        frame.childIndex++;\n        if(!this.visited.has(w)) {\n          if(this.recStack.has(w)) {\n            // Cycle detected (back edge)\n            this.finished = true;\n            this.hasCycle = true;\n            this.cycleInfo = this.detectCycleFromDFS(w);\n            return \"Cycle detected at vertex \"+w+\", topological sort impossible.\";\n          }\n          else {\n            // Push neighbor and continue DFS\n            this.dfsStack.push({\n              vertex: w,\n              neighbors: [...this.graph.edges[w]].sort(),\n              childIndex: 0\n            });\n            this.recStack.add(w);\n            this.dfsCurrent = w;\n            return \"Descending DFS to vertex \"+w+\".\";\n          }\n        }\n        else {\n          // Already visited, skip\n          return \"Skipping already visited neighbor \"+w+\".\";\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // After DFS finished, order is dfsOrder array (reverse finishing order), assign to order\n    orderFromDFS() {\n      this.order = [...this.dfsOrder];\n    }\n\n    // Cycle detection helper for DFS detected backedge w\n    // Return the cycle path from w in recursion stack\n    detectCycleFromDFS(w) {\n      // recStack has current dfs path\n      // This is a simplified approach to produce cycle path\n      // We collect vertices in dfsStack that form recursion stack\n      const cyclePath = [];\n      for(let frame of this.dfsStack) {\n        cyclePath.push(frame.vertex);\n        if(frame.vertex === w) break;\n      }\n      cyclePath.push(w);\n      return cyclePath;\n    }\n\n    // Current available nodes in Kahn (or empty for DFS because it explores internally)\n    getAvailableNodes() {\n      if(this.algo === 'kahn') return this.available;\n      if(this.algo === 'dfs') return []; \n      return [];\n    }\n  }\n\n  // GLOBAL INSTANCE\n  let sortController = null;\n\n  // Utility log appender\n  function log(msg) {\n    const now = new Date();\n    const timestamp = now.toLocaleTimeString();\n    logArea.textContent += `[${timestamp}] ${msg}\\n`;\n    logArea.scrollTop = logArea.scrollHeight;\n  }\n\n  // UI Updaters\n\n  function updateGraphDisplay() {\n    graphDisplay.textContent = graph.toAdjacencyString();\n  }\n\n  // Update all UI buttons and fields depending on graph and sort state\n  function updateGraphUIState() {\n    const hasVertices = graph.vertices.length > 0;\n\n    addVertexBtn.disabled = false;\n    clearGraphBtn.disabled = !hasVertices;\n\n    addEdgeBtn.disabled = false;\n    removeEdgeBtn.disabled = false;\n\n    loadSampleBtn.disabled = false;\n    loadAdjacencyBtn.disabled = false;\n\n    initRunBtn.disabled = !hasVertices;\n    resetSortBtn.disabled = true;\n    stepBtn.disabled = true;\n    autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    pauseAutoBtn.disabled = true;\n\n    manualPickSelect.disabled = true;\n    pickNodeBtn.disabled = true;\n\n    currentOrderDisplay.textContent = '';\n    availableNodesDisplay.textContent = '';\n    stateDisplay.textContent = '';\n    logArea.textContent = '';\n\n    manualPickSelect.innerHTML = '';\n\n    importExportArea.value = JSON.stringify({\n      vertices: [...graph.vertices].sort(),\n      edges: Object.fromEntries(Object.entries(graph.edges).map(([k,v]) => [k,[...v].sort()])),\n    }, null, 2);\n  }\n\n  // Update after initializing sortController; show available nodes, order so far, state, enable buttons accordingly\n  function updateSortUI() {\n    if (!sortController) {\n      currentOrderDisplay.textContent = '';\n      availableNodesDisplay.textContent = '';\n      stateDisplay.textContent = '';\n      stepBtn.disabled = true;\n      autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      pauseAutoBtn.disabled = true;\n      resetSortBtn.disabled = true;\n      manualPickSelect.disabled = true;\n      pickNodeBtn.disabled = true;\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const st = sortController.getStateSnapshot();\n\n    currentOrderDisplay.textContent = st.order.join(' ');\n\n    if(sortController.algo === 'kahn') {\n      availableNodesDisplay.textContent = st.available.join(' ');\n    } else if(sortController.algo === 'dfs') {\n      availableNodesDisplay.textContent = 'N/A (DFS explores internally)';\n    }\n\n    let internalStateText = '';\n\n    if(sortController.algo === 'kahn') {\n      internalStateText += \"Indegree:\\n\";\n      for(let v of graph.vertices.sort()) {\n        internalStateText += `  ${v}: ${st.indeg[v]}\\n`;\n      }\n      internalStateText += \"\\nAvailable nodes:\\n  \" + st.available.join(' ') + \"\\n\";\n      internalStateText += `\\nManual pick mode: ${st.manualPickMode ? \"YES\" : \"NO\"}\\n`;\n\n    } else if(sortController.algo === 'dfs') {\n      internalStateText += \"Visited:\\n  \" + st.visited.join(' ') + \"\\n\";\n      internalStateText += \"Recursion Stack:\\n  \" + st.recStack.join(' ') + \"\\n\";\n      internalStateText += \"DFS Stack:\\n\";\n      for(const f of st.dfsStack) {\n        internalStateText += `  Vertex: ${f.vertex}, Next neighbor idx: ${f.childIndex}\\n`;\n      }\n      internalStateText += \"\\nCurrent DFS vertex: \" + (st.dfsCurrent || \"None\") + \"\\n\";\n    }\n\n    stateDisplay.textContent = internalStateText;\n\n    stepBtn.disabled = st.finished;\n    resetSortBtn.disabled = false;\n    initRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    autoRunBtn.disabled = st.finished;\n    pauseAutoBtn.disabled = true;\n\n    if (st.manualPickMode && sortController.algo === 'kahn') {\n      manualPickSelect.disabled = false;\n      pickNodeBtn.disabled = false;\n      manualPickSelect.size = Math.min(10, st.available.length);\n      manualPickSelect.innerHTML = '';\n      for(let v of st.available) {\n        const opt = document.createElement('option');\n        opt.value = v;\n        opt.textContent = v;\n        manualPickSelect.appendChild(opt);\n      }\n      // Select first node by default\n      manualPickSelect.selectedIndex = 0;\n    } else {\n      manualPickSelect.disabled = true;\n      pickNodeBtn.disabled = true;\n      manualPickSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    }\n\n    if(st.finished) {\n      stepBtn.disabled = true;\n      autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      pauseAutoBtn.disabled = true;\n      manualPickSelect.disabled = true;\n      pickNodeBtn.disabled = true;\n      if(st.hasCycle) {\n        log(\"Cycle detected! Cycle path: \" + st.cycleInfo.join(' → '));\n      } else {\n        log(\"Topological sort completed successfully.\");\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Initialize SortController and update UI accordingly\n  function initializeSort() {\n    sortController = new SortController(graph);\n    sortController.setAlgorithm(algoSelect.value);\n    if(algoSelect.value === 'dfs') {\n      sortController.initDFS();\n    } else {\n      sortController.init();\n    }\n    updateSortUI();\n    log(\"Sort initialized with algorithm: \" + algoSelect.value);\n  }\n\n  // Step one iteration of the sorting process\n  function sortStep() {\n    if(!sortController) return;\n    let msg = \"\";\n    if(sortController.algo === 'kahn') {\n      if(sortController.manualPickMode) {\n        log(\"Waiting for manual pick, cannot step automatically.\");\n        return;\n      }\n      msg = sortController.stepKahn();\n    } else if(sortController.algo === 'dfs') {\n      msg = sortController.stepDFS();\n    }\n    log(msg);\n    updateSortUI();\n  }\n\n  // Step with manual selected node for Kahn\n  function sortManualPickStep(node) {\n    if(!sortController) return;\n    if(sortController.algo !== 'kahn') return;\n\n    if(!sortController.manualPickMode) {\n      log(\"Not in manual pick mode.\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const msg = sortController.stepKahn(node);\n    log(\"Manually picked node: \" + node);\n    log(msg);\n    updateSortUI();\n  }\n\n  // Auto run setup\n  let autoRunIntervalID = null;\n\n  function autoRunStart() {\n    if(!sortController) return;\n    const speed = parseInt(autoRunSpeedInp.value, 10);\n    if(isNaN(speed) || speed < 50) {\n      log(\"Invalid auto run speed (minimum 50 ms).\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if (autoRunIntervalID !== null) {\n      log(\"Auto run is already running.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    pauseAutoBtn.disabled = false;\n    stepBtn.disabled = true;\n    manualPickSelect.disabled = true;\n    pickNodeBtn.disabled = true;\n    sortController.autorun = true;\n\n    autoRunIntervalID = setInterval(() => {\n      if(sortController.manualPickMode) {\n        log(\"Auto run paused due to manual pick mode.\");\n        autoRunStop();\n        return;\n      }\n      if(sortController.finished) {\n        log(\"Auto run finished as sort is complete.\");\n        autoRunStop();\n        return;\n      }\n      sortStep();\n    }, speed);\n\n    log(\"Auto run started with speed \" + speed + \" ms per step.\");\n  }\n\n  function autoRunStop() {\n    if(autoRunIntervalID !== null) {\n      clearInterval(autoRunIntervalID);\n      autoRunIntervalID = null;\n      log(\"Auto run stopped.\");\n      autoRunBtn.disabled = false;\n      pauseAutoBtn.disabled = true;\n      stepBtn.disabled = sortController.finished;\n      if(sortController.manualPickMode) {\n        manualPickSelect.disabled = false;\n        pickNodeBtn.disabled = false;\n      }\n      sortController.autorun = false;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Load sample graph definitions\n  const sampleGraphs = {\n    basicDAG: {\n      vertices: ['A','B','C','D','E'],\n      edges: {\n        A: ['B','C'],\n        B: ['D'],\n        C: ['D','E'],\n        D: [],\n        E: [],\n      }\n    },\n    diamond: {\n      vertices: ['A','B','C','D'],\n      edges: {\n        A: ['B','C'],\n        B: ['D'],\n        C: ['D'],\n        D: [],\n      }\n    },\n    complex: {\n      vertices: ['A','B','C','D','E','F','G','H','I','J'],\n      edges: {\n        A: ['C','D'],\n        B: ['D','E'],\n        C: ['F'],\n        D: ['F','G'],\n        E: ['G','H'],\n        F: ['I'],\n        G: ['I','J'],\n        H: ['J'],\n        I: [],\n        J: []\n      }\n    },\n    cycle: {\n      vertices: ['A','B','C'],\n      edges: {\n        A: ['B'],\n        B: ['C'],\n        C: ['A'], // cycle C->A\n      }\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Load sample graph into graph state and update UI\n  function loadSampleGraph(name) {\n    if(!sampleGraphs[name]) {\n      alert(\"Sample graph not found.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const sample = sampleGraphs[name];\n    graph.clear();\n    for(let v of sample.vertices) graph.addVertex(v);\n    for(let v of sample.vertices) {\n      for(let w of sample.edges[v]) {\n        graph.addEdge(v,w);\n      }\n    }\n    updateGraphDisplay();\n    updateGraphUIState();\n    log(\"Loaded sample graph: \" + name);\n  }\n\n  // Parse adjacency list input - format: \"A: B C\"\n  // Returns graph object or error string\n  function parseAdjacencyList(text) {\n    const lines = text.trim().split('\\n');\n    let g = new Graph();\n    for(let line of lines) {\n      const parts = line.split(':');\n      if(parts.length !== 2) return \"Invalid line (missing colon): \" + line;\n      let v = parts[0].trim();\n      if(!v) return \"Empty vertex name on line: \" + line;\n      if(g.hasVertex(v)) {\n        return \"Duplicate vertex '\"+v+\"' in input.\";\n      }\n      g.addVertex(v);\n    }\n    // Second pass add edges\n    for(let line of lines) {\n      const parts = line.split(':');\n      let v = parts[0].trim();\n      let rhs = parts[1].trim();\n      if(rhs) {\n        const neighbors = rhs.split(/\\s+/);\n        for(let w of neighbors) {\n          if(!g.hasVertex(w)) return \"Unknown neighbor vertex '\"+w+\"' in line: \"+line;\n          g.addEdge(v,w);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    return g;\n  }\n\n  // Export graph as JSON, formatted\n  function exportGraphJSON() {\n    const obj = {\n      vertices: [...graph.vertices].sort(),\n      edges: {}\n    };\n    for(let v of graph.vertices) {\n      obj.edges[v] = [...graph.edges[v]].sort();\n    }\n    return JSON.stringify(obj, null, 2);\n  }\n\n  // Import graph JSON - return Graph instance or error string\n  function importGraphJSON(jsonText) {\n    let parsed;\n    try {\n      parsed = JSON.parse(jsonText);\n    } catch(e) {\n      return \"Invalid JSON syntax.\";\n    }\n    if(!parsed.vertices || !Array.isArray(parsed.vertices))\n      return \"JSON must have a 'vertices' array.\";\n    if(!parsed.edges || typeof parsed.edges !== 'object')\n      return \"JSON must have an 'edges' object.\";\n    let g = new Graph();\n    for(let v of parsed.vertices) {\n      if(typeof v !== 'string') return \"All vertices must be strings.\";\n      g.addVertex(v);\n    }\n    for(let v in parsed.edges) {\n      if(!g.hasVertex(v)) return \"Edges contain unknown vertex '\"+v+\"'.\";\n      const targets = parsed.edges[v];\n      if(!Array.isArray(targets)) return \"Edges for vertex '\"+v+\"' must be an array.\";\n      for(let w of targets) {\n        if(!g.hasVertex(w)) return \"Edges for vertex '\"+v+\"' contain unknown target '\"+w+\"'.\";\n        g.addEdge(v,w);\n      }\n    }\n    return g;\n  }\n\n  // Button Event Listeners\n\n  addVertexBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const v = vertexNameInp.value.trim();\n    if(!v) {\n      alert(\"Enter vertex name.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if(graph.hasVertex(v)) {\n      alert(\"Vertex '\"+v+\"' already exists.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    graph.addVertex(v);\n    updateGraphDisplay();\n    updateGraphUIState();\n    log(\"Added vertex '\"+v+\"'.\");\n  });\n\n  clearGraphBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(!confirm(\"Clear the entire graph?\")) return;\n    graph.clear();\n    updateGraphDisplay();\n    updateGraphUIState();\n    log(\"Graph cleared.\");\n  });\n\n  addEdgeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const from = fromVertexInp.value.trim();\n    const to = toVertexInp.value.trim();\n    if(!from || !to) {\n      alert(\"Enter both 'From' and 'To' vertex names.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!graph.hasVertex(from)) {\n      alert(\"Vertex '\"+from+\"' does not exist.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!graph.hasVertex(to)) {\n      alert(\"Vertex '\"+to+\"' does not exist.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if(from === to) {\n      if(!confirm(\"Add a self-loop edge? This will create a cycle.\")) return;\n    }\n    if(graph.addEdge(from, to)) {\n      updateGraphDisplay();\n      updateGraphUIState();\n      log(\"Added edge '\"+from+\"' → '\"+to+\"'.\");\n    } else {\n      alert(\"Edge '\"+from+\"' → '\"+to+\"' already exists.\");\n    }\n  });\n\n  removeEdgeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const from = fromVertexInp.value.trim();\n    const to = toVertexInp.value.trim();\n    if(!from || !to) {\n      alert(\"Enter both 'From' and 'To' vertex names.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if(graph.removeEdge(from, to)) {\n      updateGraphDisplay();\n      updateGraphUIState();\n      log(\"Removed edge '\"+from+\"' → '\"+to+\"'.\");\n    } else {\n      alert(\"Edge '\"+from+\"' → '\"+to+\"' does not exist.\");\n    }\n  });\n\n  loadSampleBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const val = loadSampleSelect.value;\n    if(!val) {\n      alert(\"Select a sample graph to load.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    loadSampleGraph(val);\n  });\n\n  loadAdjacencyBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const text = pasteAdjacencyArea.value;\n    if(!text.trim()) {\n      alert(\"Paste adjacency list input first.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const res = parseAdjacencyList(text);\n    if(typeof res === 'string') {\n      alert(\"Error parsing adjacency list:\\n\" + res);\n      return;\n    }\n    // Success\n    graph.clear();\n    for(let v of res.vertices) graph.addVertex(v);\n    for(let v of res.vertices) {\n      for(let w of res.edges[v]) {\n        graph.addEdge(v,w);\n      }\n    }\n    updateGraphDisplay();\n    updateGraphUIState();\n    log(\"Loaded graph from adjacency list.\");\n  });\n\n  initRunBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(!graph.vertices.length) {\n      alert(\"Graph is empty.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    initializeSort();\n  });\n\n  stepBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    sortStep();\n  });\n\n  autoRunBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    autoRunStart();\n  });\n\n  pauseAutoBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    autoRunStop();\n  });\n\n  resetSortBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    sortController = null;\n    updateSortUI();\n    initRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    log(\"Sort reset. Ready to initialize.\");\n  });\n\n  pickNodeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(!sortController) {\n      alert(\"Sort not initialized.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!sortController.manualPickMode) {\n      alert(\"Not expecting manual pick now.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const sel = manualPickSelect.value;\n    if(!sel) {\n      alert(\"Select a node from dropdown.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    sortManualPickStep(sel);\n  });\n\n  algoSelect.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    // Reset sort state\n    sortController = null;\n    updateSortUI();\n    initRunBtn.disabled = graph.vertices.length === 0;\n    log(\"Algorithm changed to: \"+algoSelect.value);\n  });\n\n  autoRunSpeedInp.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    if(autoRunIntervalID !== null) {\n      autoRunStop();\n      autoRunStart();\n    }\n  });\n\n  exportGraphBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const json = exportGraphJSON();\n    importExportArea.value = json;\n    log(\"Graph exported as JSON to the text area.\");\n  });\n\n  importGraphBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    let text = importExportArea.value.trim();\n    if(!text) {\n      alert(\"Paste graph JSON into the text area first.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const res = importGraphJSON(text);\n    if(typeof res === 'string') {\n      alert(\"Error importing graph JSON:\\n\" + res);\n      return;\n    }\n    graph.clear();\n    for(let v of res.vertices) graph.addVertex(v);\n    for(let v of res.vertices) {\n      for(let w of res.edges[v]) {\n        graph.addEdge(v,w);\n      }\n    }\n    updateGraphDisplay();\n    updateGraphUIState();\n    log(\"Graph imported from JSON.\");\n  });\n\n  // Initial Setup\n  updateGraphDisplay();\n  updateGraphUIState();\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
